     = 26\n| club-update          = 28 April 2018 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Theo Anthony Lewis''' (born 10 August 1991) is an English [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder]] for [[Vanarama National League]] Premier Division side [[Havant and Waterlooville F.C.|Havant and Waterlooville]].\n\n==Club career==\nLewis started his career as a youth player at [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] before joining [[Cheltenham Town F.C.|Cheltenham Town]] for the [[2007-08 in English football|2007\u201308]] season.<ref name=\"First team: Theo Lewis\">{{cite web\n| title = First team: Theo Lewis\n| url = http://www.ctfc.com/page/ProfilesDetail/0,,10434~47077,00.html\n| publisher = Cheltenham Town F.C.\n| accessdate = 2009-07-19}}</ref> He made his first team debut in a [[Football League One|League One]] match against [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]] in the 3\u20130 away defeat on 28 April 2009, replacing [[Kyle Haynes]] as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in the 73rd minute.<ref name=\"Scunthorpe 3-0 Cheltenham\">{{cite news\n| title = Scunthorpe 3\u20130 Cheltenham\n| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_2/8010801.stm\n| publisher = BBC Sport\n| date = 2009-04-28\n| accessdate = 2009-07-19}}</ref><ref name=\"sufc-ctfc\">{{cite web\n| title = Fixtures/results: Scunthorpe 3&nbsp;\u2013 0 Cheltenham\n| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/results3.sd?gameid=584231\n| publisher = Soccerbase\n| accessdate = 2009-07-19}}</ref>\n\nHaving been a squad player for much of [[2009\u201310 Football League Two|2009\u201310]] and [[2010\u201311 Cheltenham Town F.C. season|2010\u201311]] seasons, Lewis found himself out of the first team picture in [[2011\u201312 Cheltenham Town F.C. season|2011\u201312]] and went out on loan to rivals [[Gloucester City A.F.C.|Gloucester City]] on 12 March 2012, originally for a month which was extended to the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite web| title = City welcome Lewis on loan| url = http://www.gloucestercityafc.com/city-welcome-lewis-on-loan/| publisher = Gloucester City A.F.C.| date = 9 March 2012}}</ref> After the end of Gloucester's season, Lewis returned to Cheltenham and made his only League Two appearance in their final league game against [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]]. In May 2012, Lewis was released by Cheltenham after the expiry of his contract.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yates rings changes at Robins |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/12691/7785597/Yates-rings-changes-at-Robins|newspaper=Sky Sports|date=29 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nFollowing his release from Cheltenham, Theo trialled at [[Salisbury City F.C.|Salisbury City]]. This proved successful as he later signed for the club after impressing manager [[Darrell Clarke]] with his footballing ability as well as his enthusiasm and professionalism. He played in the majority of matches during the 2012\u201313 season as a midfielder. He signed a new deal in the pre-season period ahead of the 2013\u201314 season, keeping him with Salisbury for another year.\n\nFollowing financial troubles, [[Salisbury City F.C.|Salisbury City]] were forced to offload a number of their players during the summer and as a result Lewis went on to sign for [[Woking F.C.|Woking]] for the 2014\u201315 season.\n\nTheo unexpectedly left [[Woking F.C.|Woking]] at the start of the new year once the transfer window opened. He went on to sign for [[Ebbsfleet United F.C.|Ebbsfleet United]] for an undisclosed fee. After failing to make an impression under Ebbsfleet United manager [[Daryl McMahon]], Lewis joined [[National League South]] side [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]] on a two-month loan in November 2015.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Theo wings his way to Hawks |url=http://ebbsfleetunited.co.uk/theo-wings-his-way-to-hawks/ |publisher=Ebbsfleet United F.C. |date=10 November 2015 |accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref> After numerous loan extensions to Lewis's spell with Havant & Waterlooville, his stay was made permanent in July 2016.<ref>{{Cite news |title=HAWKS Sign Theo Lewis |url=http://www.havantandwaterloovillefc.co.uk/articles/2016/07/08/hawks-sign-theo-lewis.html |publisher=Havant & Waterlooville F.C. |date=8 July 2016 |accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 28 April 2018.<ref>{{Cite news |title=T. Lewis |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/theo-lewis/69399/ |publisher=Soccerway |accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref>}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Football League Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\" valign=\"center\"|[[Cheltenham Town F.C.|Cheltenham Town]]\n|[[2008\u201309 Football League One|2008\u201309]]\n|[[Football League One|League One]]\n|2||0||0||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Football League Two|2009\u201310]]\n|[[Football League Two|League Two]]\n|15||0||1||1||0||0||0||0||16||1\n|-\n|[[2010\u201311 Football League Two|2010\u201311]]\n|League Two\n|21||0||0||0||0||0||1<ref group=lower-alpha name=FLT>Appearance(s) in [[Football League Trophy]]</ref>||0||22||0\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Football League Two|2011\u201312]]\n|League Two\n|1||0||0||0||0||0||2<ref group=lower-alpha name=FLT/>||0||3||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!39!!0!!1!!1!!0!!0!!3!!0!!43!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Gloucester City A.F.C.|Gloucester City]] (loan)\n|[[2011\u201312 Football Conference|2011\u201312]]\n|[[Conference South]]\n|9||3||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0||9||3\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" valign=\"center\"|[[Salisbury City F.C.|Salisbury City]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Football Conference|2012\u201313]]\n|Conference South\n|38||2||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||4<ref group=lower-alpha name=FAT>Appearance(s) in [[FA Trophy]]</ref><ref group=lower-alpha na